whence abrupt Excite they oft, as forms of beauty rise, The scenes at hand, the regions ruled by love.
Then springs the tender tumour, the warm wish Full o'er the foe, the luscious wound who deals, With dexterous aim to pour the high-wrought charge, And full contending in the genial fight.
So falls the victim on the part assailed:
With the red blood the glistening bruise so swells;
And o'er th' assassin flows the tide he draws.
So he who feels the shaft of love propell'd
From the dear form that charms him, towards the spot Aims, whence the wound proceeds;
supreme he pants
