but from types alike Free to each term, yet ever new combined, Flows the vast change, th' harmonious system flows.
Thus, through the world, the primal seeds of all, To all things common, re-arranged diverse, In myriad forms shoot forth ;
and herbs, and men, And trees umbrageous own the same fixt source.
