So, from the juice of BACCHUS, when flies off Its flower ethereal, from the light perfume
When mounts the essential spirit, or from man Th' excreted lymph exhales-the curious eye Nought marks diminished,-the same weight survives, Th' same fixt bulk, since from minutest seeds Springs the light scent, the ethereal spirit springs.
