the vital air Still breathes, and lingers out his joyless hours.
Thus, though the visual orb be wounded, still, If safe the central pupil, sight remains:
Where'er descends the blow, should this alone Elude its vengeance, ruin ne'er ensues.
But, if of this the least existent point Once suffer, though the total else escape, Light fails immediate, and dread darkness reigns.
Such the connexion 'twixt the soul and mind.
