And seest thou not, from many a fact hence proved, That through the total body lives the soul, And e'en in body severs, seed from seed, Ere thence expelled, and scattered into air ?
E'en during life the fractured soul seems oft From force abrupt half-hurried from her home;
Each vital function failing, and the face, As though in death, all pallid, changed, and wan.
