In size scarce vary from the form they show.
Nor deem it strange that so minute a sun Should pour forth flame sufficient heaven to fill, And earth, and ocean, and whatever exists Tinge with its glittering dew;
for, from abroad
The myriad seeds of fire dispersed at large Through all things, here as to their fountain flow, And hence well forth o'er all th' exulting world
