How rare the frame of all things, as erewhile Conspicuous proved we in our earliest strain.
A theme, though ever useful, useful most Found, when compelled, as now, to re-affirm That nought exists but matter mixt with void.
For, first, the roofs of rocky caverns sweat With dews, and crystals;
and the frame of man Throws through each pore the perspirable lymph.
